    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-01-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-01-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="1294"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1294">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.115/42.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Miller</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Tampico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-01-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 9, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Consular Agent, Tuxpam, reports that Federal authorities Tuxpam have demanded
                    payment 70,000 Mexican dollars from business men and foreign companies, offer as
                    excuse that Federal troops have not been paid and that there is reason to fear
                    that they will join revolutionists. Amount collected and receipts given January
                    7th.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Miller</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
